full_text: UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE Form Approved Immigration and Naturalization Service Budget Bureau No. 43-R399.1 P. O. BOX 52-622 MIAMI, FLORIDA Petition No. 432-P-17983 AR # 10 891 712 NOV 9 1962 Date H- 17982 D- 17984 Mrs. Milada Antonia Stangel, 900 S. Highland Avenue, Clearwater, Florida. Dear Mrs. Stangel: You are hereby notified to appear for final hearing on your petition for naturalization on NOV 16 1962 at U.S. DISTRICT COURT, POST OFFICE BUILDING, TAMPA, FLORIDA Please report promptly at 10:00 A. M. Your witnesses need.NOT come with you. YOU MUST BRING WITH YOU THE ITEMS MARKED BELOW: This letter, WITH ALL OF THE QUESTIONS ON THE OTHER SIDE ANSWERED. Alien Registration Receipt Card. Any Immigration documents you may have. MEN WILL WEAR COATS If you cannot come to this final hearing, return this letter right away and state when you will be ready to go ahead with your case. Very truly yours, Joseph Minton Deputy District Director Form N-445 (Rev. 2-1-62) (SEE OTHER SIDE) GP O 9 28 39 7
